Speech synthesizer SAM ran in real time on the 1 MHz 6502 in Apple II and C64. The SPC700 is a 1 MHz 65C02 with a reshuffled instruction encoding and a minor difference in the PLA instruction.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed May 21, 2014 11:03 am</p><hr />
